 both classes, including the order they are serialized. If there's a failure in the superclass, I wonder if the subclass will ever get processed. Exploring the use of Externalizable might be worth considering, but hmm, I think I'll need to inspect the serialization order further.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Superclass Serialization**\\n\\nI’m considering how to make superclass fields serializable by updating the loadLocks object array to use Serializable objects, but reflection is prohibited in tests. Could using a system property for Runtime processors help? Not sure. Maybe I should look into making the subclass Caching relevant, but without an active class like Soft, I’d still need to access private writeObject, which a standard ObjectOutputStream cannot do due to the non-serializable superclass. I might need to handle the readObject method carefully while deserializing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_dpvlpFl1PBTJBNPVfhsAeRHr|fc_0452a51efe222f950169f52cc1dd44819f98a93a55332c1723", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/SoftCachingModuleScriptProviderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(outputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(provider);\n        }\n", "newText": "        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new SerializableLockReplacingObjectOutputStream(outputStream)) {\n            objectOutputStream.writeObject(provider);\n        }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class SingleUseModuleSourceProvider implements ModuleSourceProvider, Serializable {\n", "newText": "    private static final class SerializableLockReplacingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        SerializableLockReplacingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream) throws IOException {\n            super(outputStream);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object != null && object.getClass() == Object.class) {\n                return \"serializable-lock\";\n            }\n            return object;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class SingleUseModuleSourceProvider implements ModuleSourceProvider, Serializable {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3736, "output": 1456, "cacheRead": 45568, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50760, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777675437690, "responseId": "resp_0452a51efe222f950169f52cae4300819f89ff82efdd5ecca8"}}
