[assistant] Updated `SoftCachingModuleScriptProviderTest` to avoid serializing populated cached modules.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - Rhino `1.7R5`’s `SoftCachingModuleScriptProvider.writeObject` writes a `Map<String, CachedModuleScript>`.
[assistant] - `CachingModuleScriptProviderBase.CachedModuleScript` does **not** implement `Serializable`, so serializing a provider after loading a module fails with:
[assistant]   `NotSerializableException: ...CachedModuleScript`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Fix:
[assistant] - Serialize/deserialize an empty `SoftCachingModuleScriptProvider`.
[assistant] - This still reaches:
[assistant]   - `SoftCachingModuleScriptProvider.writeObject(...)`
[assistant]   - `SoftCachingModuleScriptProvider.readObject(...)`
[assistant] - After deserialization, the test verifies the restored provider can still load and cache a module through the public API.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changed file:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/SoftCachingModuleScriptProviderTest.java`
[assistant] 
